  <Subject Subject_ID="300104620">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300024600</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>power producing equipment [300024600], equipment by process [300024659], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Use to refer to devices that convert chemical energy into voltaic electrical current. Strictest usage applies this term only to devices of two or more galvanic cells, but American English usage is most commonly applied to the single-cell variety.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>將化學能量轉換為伏特電流的裝置。最嚴格的用法專指兩顆或兩顆以上的直流電池裝置，但在美式英語中常指單顆電池的裝置。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wird für ein Gerät verwendet, das chemische Energie in elektrischen Strom umwandelt. Im engsten Sinne wird dieser Begriff nur auf Geräte mit zwei oder mehr galvanischen Zellen verwendet, doch der Gebrauch im Englischen ist meist allgemein bezogen auf die Einzellvariante.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken om te verwijzen naar apparaten die chemische energie omzetten in elektrische stroom. Strikt genomen is deze term alleen van toepassing op apparaten met twee of meer galvanische cellen, maar in het gangbaar spraakgebruik wordt de term het meest gebruikt voor de variant met één cel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
